This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of semantic image segmentation. The use of Deep Learning and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) also suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of code availability and practical applications suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
